📄 2. Project Overview
The Sustainable Smart City Assistant is an AI-driven application developed to support smart city planning and governance. The assistant uses the IBM Granite LLM model for providing intelligent responses, extracting insights from documents, and addressing citizen queries related to sustainable urban living.
________________________________________
🎯 3. Objective
The goal of this project is to enhance the quality of urban governance and citizen engagement by leveraging a state-of-the-art Large Language Model (LLM). The assistant aims to:
•	Simplify access to sustainable city policies and documents.
•	Assist citizens by answering questions related to city planning.
•	Enable quick and intelligent insights for city administrators.
________________________________________
⚡ 4. Technologies Used
•	LLM Model: IBM Granite LLM
•	Frameworks:
o	Backend: Python (Flask / FastAPI)
o	Frontend: React.js / Next.js
•	Database: MongoDB / PostgreSQL
•	Deployment: Docker, Kubernetes (optional)
•	Additional Tools: IBM Watsonx Services, GitHub, Postman
________________________________________
🛠️ 5. Features
✅ Intelligent Q/A on Sustainable Development Regulations
✅ Policy Document Summarization
✅ Interactive Chat Interface for Users
✅ Provides Suggestions and Insights for Smart Cities
✅ Supports Multilingual Queries (Future Scope)
________________________________________
🗂️ 6. Project Architecture
High-Level Architecture:
rust
CopyEdit
User --> Frontend (React.js) --> Backend (Flask / FastAPI) --> 
    IBM Granite LLM Model --> Database (MongoDB / PostgreSQL)
________________________________________
🚀 7. Key Use Cases
•	Helping urban planners quickly access relevant sustainable planning documents.
•	Helping citizens understand sustainable policies and regulations.
•	Helping city administrators make data-driven decisions.
________________________________________
📋 8. Prerequisites
•	Node.js / npm installed
•	Python 3.9+
•	IBM Watsonx or IBM Granite LLM account
•	Git for version control
•	MongoDB / PostgreSQL database
•	9. Installation & Setup
1️⃣  Clone the Repository:
git clone https://github.com/your-repo/sustainable-smart-city-assistant.git

2️⃣ Install Dependencies:
# Frontend
cd frontend && npm install

# Backend
cd backend && pip install -r requirements.txt

3️⃣ Configure Environment Variables:
Create .env files for:
•	IBM Granite LLM API_KEY
•	Database Connection String
•	Frontend Backend API URL
4️⃣ Run the Project:
# Backend
uvicorn app:app --reload

# Frontend
npm run dev

